WEBVTT

00:00.930 --> 00:02.579
- WHEN IT COMES TO MA'ITERS
OF BULLYING--

00:02.620 --> 00:04.645
- SO SYDNEY'S PICKING
ON MELODY?

00:04.690 --> 00:08.103
- JOEL, UM,
I'M SEEING SOMEONE.

00:08.140 --> 00:10.449
- OLIVER ROME FREAKED OUT
AND LEFI' THE SOUND CHECK.

00:10.490 --> 00:13.414
- GET IN THE CAR
AND GET TO THE SHOW--OLIVER!

00:14.490 --> 00:17.072
- WHEN RUBY IS WITH YOU,
SHE'S WITH YOU.

00:17.120 --> 00:18.496
I DON'T EVEN WANT SARAH AROUND.

00:18.530 --> 00:19.633
DO WE UNDERSTAND EACH OTHER?

00:20.570 --> 00:21.525
- SURGERY WENT WELL.

00:21.570 --> 00:22.662
THERE WERE NO COMPLICATIONS.

00:22.710 --> 00:25.497
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO SEE
HOW HE RESPONDS.

00:28.370 --> 00:29.462
[text alert]

00:45.560 --> 00:47.073
- WHAT?

00:56.810 --> 00:58.254
AHEM!

00:58.290 --> 01:02.329
[clears throat loudly]

01:02.370 --> 01:05.601
[coughs loudly]

01:05.650 --> 01:07.470
DID I WAKE YOU?
- WHAT TIME IS IT?

01:07.510 --> 01:09.432
- OH, IT'S BEAUTIFUL OUT.

01:09.480 --> 01:10.754
WE OVERSLEPT, AND YOU GOTTA
GET TO THE BREAKFAST,

01:12.410 --> 01:13.718
- BRUNCH.
- OKAY.

01:13.760 --> 01:15.512
- IT'S 11:30.
- IS IT BRUNCH? YEAH?

01:15.550 --> 01:16.721
AH, YOU'RE UP NOW. I'VE GOT
A CLEANING LADY COMING TOO.

01:16.760 --> 01:18.239
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS?
I FORGOT.

01:18.280 --> 01:20.100
- AT 7:00?
- YEAH. THAT'S PROBABLY HER NOW.

01:20.140 --> 01:22.529
SHE'S A LITTLE EARLY.
I'LL LET HER DO THE FRONT ROOM.

01:22.560 --> 01:24.551
GO TO SLEEP. I DON'T KNOW--
I'M SORRY TO WAKE YOU.

01:24.600 --> 01:25.521
WHY DID I DO THAT?

01:31.430 --> 01:32.465
HEY!

01:32.500 --> 01:33.569
- HEY. GOOD MORNING.
- HEY.

01:33.610 --> 01:35.498
- THANK YOU FOR TAKING HER.
- YEAH, NO PROBLEM.

01:35.540 --> 01:36.814
ALL RIGHT.
RU BY--

01:36.850 --> 01:38.602
- I HAVE AN EARLY THING, SO--
- WELL, AND YOU'RE IN A RUSH.

01:38.650 --> 01:40.265
I GOT IT. IT'S ALL GOOD.
- OKAY.

01:40.300 --> 01:42.234
- YEAH. YEAH.

01:45.890 --> 01:47.096
- HI.
- YEAH.

01:47.140 --> 01:50.268
- I'M SORRY--I DON'T--HE SAID
IT WAS THE CLEANING LADY.

01:50.310 --> 01:51.618
I--HELLO.

01:51.660 --> 01:53.514
GOOD MORNING, SARAH.
SORRY.

01:53.560 --> 01:55.380
- NO, SHE KNOWS WHO YOU ARE.
YOU'RE SARAH.

01:55.420 --> 01:57.103
HER DAUGHTER'S PREGNANT SO SHE'S
GONNA HAVE BREAKFAST WITH US.

02:01.250 --> 02:05.562
- I'LL JUST PUT SOME CLOTHES ON.

02:05.600 --> 02:06.419
- "ROME ALONE.

02:06.470 --> 02:10.224
ROME COURTED
BY SUB MODO RECORDS?"

02:10.260 --> 02:11.704
ARE YOU KIDDING ME--
- BODY SLAM!

02:11.750 --> 02:15.538
- AAH!
JABBAR! COME ON!

02:15.580 --> 02:16.649
- HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

02:16.680 --> 02:18.238
- YOU CAN'T JUST JUMP
ON MY RIBS.

02:18.270 --> 02:20.500
- WHAT HAPPENED?
ARE YOU HURT?

02:20.550 --> 02:22.438
- I MEAN, MY RIBS
ARE JUST BRUISED.

02:22.480 --> 02:23.617
IT'S NOT--IT'S ALREADY HEALED.

02:23.660 --> 02:25.719
- WHY ARE THEY JUST--WAIT,
WHY ARE THEY JUST BRUISED?

02:25.760 --> 02:27.512
- I GOT IN A LITTLE--

02:27.560 --> 02:29.619
- WHAT--LI'|'|'LE WHAT?

02:29.660 --> 02:30.831
- I GOT IN A LITTLE
MOTORCYCLE SPILL.

02:30.870 --> 02:32.599
- WHOA.
- WHAT HAPPENED?

02:32.630 --> 02:33.904
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
A LITTLE MOTORCYCLE SPILL?

02:33.940 --> 02:35.453
THAT DOESN'T LOOK
LIKE A LITTLE MOTORCYCLE SPILL.

02:35.500 --> 02:37.525
- IT WAS A LITTLE--
- HAVE YOU SEEN A DOCTOR YET?

02:37.570 --> 02:38.764
- WHAT AM I GONNA SEE
A DOCTOR ABOUT?

02:38.810 --> 02:40.391
THEY'RE JUST BRUISED.
- HOW DO YOU KNOW?

02:40.430 --> 02:41.943
'CAUSE YOU'RE NOT A DOCTOR.
- WELL, IF THEY WERE BROKEN,

02:41.980 --> 02:44.289
THERE WOULD BE, LIKE, SHARDS
AND STUFF STABBED IN MY LUNGS.

02:44.330 --> 02:46.469
- YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW--WHY
DIDN'T YOU TELL ME THIS EARLIER?

02:46.510 --> 02:47.772
YOU NEED TO SEE A DOCTOR
FOR THAT.

02:47.820 --> 02:48.889
- I'M SORRY I YELLED.
IT'S FINE.

02:48.920 --> 02:50.501
I'M TOUGH.
IT'LL BE OKAY.

02:50.540 --> 02:52.679
- NO, IT'S MORE LIKE,
"WE DON'T RIDE MOTORCYCLES.:

02:52.720 --> 02:53.744
- SORRY I YELLED.
- THAT'S THE LESSON HERE.

02:53.790 --> 02:55.473
- DON'T RIDE MOTORCYCLES.

02:55.520 --> 02:57.511
- RIGHT.
BUT YOU'RE STILL TOUGH.

02:57.550 --> 02:59.199
- OKAY, I BET YOU HE WASN'T
TOUGH WHEN HE HIT THE GROUND.

02:59.240 --> 03:00.616
YOU DIDN'T SOUND TOUGH
A FEW MINUTES AGO.

03:00.660 --> 03:02.378
- I DIDN'T CRY, SO--
- YEAH, RIGHT.

03:02.420 --> 03:04.479
- YOU WOULD'VE CRIED.

03:04.520 --> 03:07.409
SHE WOULDN'T CRY.
YOU WANT TO SEE A TRAITOR?

03:07.460 --> 03:09.690
RIGHT THERE. OLIVER ROME.

03:09.740 --> 03:11.492
- SO HERE WE
HAVE OUR COMMON ROOM

03:11.530 --> 03:13.566
WHERE MOST OF OUR GROUP
ACTIVITIES TAKE PLACE.

03:13.600 --> 03:16.398
THIS IS WHERE YOU GUYS ALL
HANG OUT AND SORT OF CONVERSE

03:16.430 --> 03:19.319
AND TALK WITH EACH OTHER, AND--

03:19.370 --> 03:22.533
DOWN HERE WE HAVE YOUR CORE
CLASSROOMS--CLASSROOMS A AND B.

03:22.580 --> 03:25.879
- COOL.
- AND LUNCH IS HERE AT 12:00.

03:25.920 --> 03:28.616
HEY, BUDDY.
MAX, THIS IS DYLAN JONES.

03:28.650 --> 03:29.787
SHE'S OUR NEWEST STUDENT.

03:29.830 --> 03:31.377
THIS IS MAX.

03:31.410 --> 03:33.617
- ADHD
AND GENERAL BEHAVIORAL ISSUES.

03:33.660 --> 03:35.821
WHAT ARE YOU IN FOR?

03:35.870 --> 03:36.894
ALL RIGHT.

03:36.940 --> 03:38.441
I GOT KICKED
OUT OF MY OLD SCHOOL.

03:38.490 --> 03:40.037
THIS MAKES NUMBER FOUR.

03:40.080 --> 03:41.559
IS IT AS MISERABLE HERE
AS EVERYBODY SAYS?

03:44.630 --> 03:46.518
NONVERBAL, HUH? COOL.

03:46.570 --> 03:48.629
- ACTUALLY, HE'S--

03:48.670 --> 03:52.458
HE'S A GOOD KID.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

03:52.500 --> 03:53.876
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'VE HEARD
ABOUT CHAMBERS,

03:53.920 --> 03:55.774
BUT I KNOW
THAT THIS IS AN AWESOME SCHOOL,

03:55.820 --> 03:56.889
AND I'M REALLY PROUD OF IT.

03:56.920 --> 03:58.956
I THINK THIS IS GONNA BE
A REALLY GOOD FIT FOR YOU.

03:58.990 --> 04:01.504
- THAT'S WHAT THEY ALL SAY.

04:04.480 --> 04:06.516
- OKAY NOW, YOU WAIT.
- I KNOW.

04:06.550 --> 04:08.438
- I'M GONNA HELP YOU.
- OKAY.

04:10.490 --> 04:14.449
OH, GOD.

04:14.490 --> 04:17.550
- HEY, I THINK SAID
I WAS GONNA HELP YOU.

04:17.600 --> 04:19.318
- YEAH.
- HEY, POP.

04:19.360 --> 04:20.839
HOW ARE YOU?

04:20.880 --> 04:22.074
LOOKING GOOD.

04:22.120 --> 04:24.532
- GOSH, MILLIE.
YOU KNOW--NO FUSS HERE.

04:24.570 --> 04:25.491
- THERE'S NO FUSS.
- HEY.

04:25.540 --> 04:26.222
- YOU JUST NEED A LITTLE HELP,
YOU KNOW?

04:26.260 --> 04:27.534
- YEAH, WE GOT YOU ALL SET UP.

04:27.570 --> 04:28.707
MOM AND I HAVE DISCUSSED IT.

04:28.750 --> 04:30.297
WE PUT YOU BED THERE
IN THE LIVING ROOM.

04:30.330 --> 04:31.774
YOU GOT YOUR OWN SUITE.
- YEAH, SO YOU WON'T HAVE TO...

04:31.820 --> 04:32.809
- I'VE GOT A SUITE?
- YEAH.

04:32.850 --> 04:34.738
- WALK UP THE STAIRS.
- NOW, HOW ABOUT THAT?

04:34.790 --> 04:36.576
FIGURED IT'D BE BEST
IF YOU HAD YOUR KITCHEN,

04:36.620 --> 04:38.884
AND BEDROOM, AND BATHROOM
ALL ON ONE LEVEL.

04:38.930 --> 04:40.374
- ALL RIGHT?
- OKAY? YOU GOT IT?

04:40.410 --> 04:41.581
- YEP, I GOT IT.

04:41.620 --> 04:42.473
- OKAY.
- OH, GOD.

04:42.520 --> 04:44.067
- OKAY, JUST REMEMBER
THAT THE DOCTOR

04:44.110 --> 04:46.510
SAID YOU HAVE TO WORK UP
TO WALKING AROUND THE BLOCK.

04:46.560 --> 04:47.936
YOU'VE GO'I'I'A
TAKE IT EASY, FIRST.

04:47.970 --> 04:50.347
- YEP.
- RIGHT.

04:50.390 --> 04:52.449
- DOING GREAT.

05:00.810 --> 05:04.701
YOU OKAY?

05:04.750 --> 05:06.536
- YEAH.
- WANNA HEAD IN?

05:06.580 --> 05:07.979
- YOU READY?

05:08.030 --> 05:10.055
- ALL RIGHT, LET ME
HELP YOU OUT A LITTLE BIT.

05:10.100 --> 05:11.476
- OKAY.
- ALL RIGHT.

05:11.510 --> 05:13.717
- OKAY.

05:13.760 --> 05:16.513
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

05:16.550 --> 05:18.996
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

05:19.040 --> 05:21.508
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

05:21.560 --> 05:23.721
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

05:23.770 --> 05:26.523
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

05:26.560 --> 05:28.551
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

05:28.600 --> 05:30.875
AND MAY YOU STAY

05:30.910 --> 05:33.561
FOREVER YOUNG

05:33.600 --> 05:36.046
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

05:36.090 --> 05:38.467
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

05:38.510 --> 05:40.819
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

05:40.850 --> 05:43.023
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

05:43.060 --> 05:45.813
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

05:45.860 --> 05:47.999
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

05:48.030 --> 05:49.964
AND MAY YOU STAY

05:50.000 --> 05:52.651
FOREVER YOUNG

05:52.690 --> 05:54.931
MAY YOU STAY

05:54.970 --> 05:58.451
FOREVER YOUNG

06:00.700 --> 06:02.429
- HAVE YOU SEEN
THIS OLIVER ROME ARTICLE?

06:02.460 --> 06:03.427
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

06:03.460 --> 06:05.041
- YOU READ PITCHFORK.
- WE'RE SCREWED.

06:05.080 --> 06:06.945
- I THOUGHT YOU GOT ALL
YOUR MUSIC NEWS FROM STARBUCKS.

06:06.980 --> 06:08.390
- CROSBY, THIS ISN'T
A JOKE, OKAY?

06:08.430 --> 06:09.738
- YEAH, OBVIOUSLY IT'S--

06:09.780 --> 06:10.599
- AND NONE OF THIS WOULD BE
HAPPENING, BY THE WAY,

06:10.640 --> 06:11.846
IF YOU WERE ABLE
TO KEEP HIM ON TOUR

06:11.880 --> 06:12.915
LIKE YOU SAID YOU'D BE
ABLE TO.

06:12.950 --> 06:14.190
- WELL, AGAIN--I--OKAY, I--

06:14.230 --> 06:15.015
- THAT TOUR'S KEEPING
THE LIGHTS ON, HERE.

06:15.060 --> 06:16.846
- YES, I UNDERSTAND THAT,
OKAY?

06:16.890 --> 06:19.404
WELL, HOW MUCH CAN HE DO?
WE HAVE A CONTRACT.

06:19.440 --> 06:21.192
- YEAH, WE HAVE A CONTRACT
WITH ASHES OF ROME.

06:21.240 --> 06:24.926
WE DON'T HAVE A CONTRACT WITH
OLIVER ROME, THE SOLO ARTIST.

06:24.970 --> 06:26.096
- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

06:26.140 --> 06:27.789
- NO. WE HAVE CONTRACT
WITH THE BAND.

06:27.830 --> 06:29.411
- OLIVER ROME IS ASHES OF ROME.

06:29.450 --> 06:30.963
WHAT, YOU DIDN'T SIGN ANYTHING
WITH HIM?

06:31.010 --> 06:32.898
- IT'S A BAND.
HOW WAS I SUPPOSED TO KNOW THAT

06:32.940 --> 06:35.454
HE'D TRY AND GO SIGN UP AS
A SOLO ARTIST WITH SUB MODO?

06:35.490 --> 06:38.141
- LISTEN TO ME, YOU SCREWED
THE POOCH ON THIS BIG TIME.

06:38.190 --> 06:39.282
- I SCREWED THE--

06:39.320 --> 06:41.140
YOU SAID YOU WERE GONNA
BE ABLE TO KEEP HIM ON TOUR.

06:41.190 --> 06:42.396
- THAT'S LIKE NOT HAVING
MICHAEL JACKSON

06:42.430 --> 06:45.081
IN THE, WELL, JACKSON FIVE.
- WELL, I TRIED CALLING HIM.

06:45.120 --> 06:46.530
I CAN'T REACH HIM, SO
YOU TELL ME WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO.

06:46.570 --> 06:50.643
THIS IS ON YOU.
IT'S NOT ON ME.

06:50.680 --> 06:54.571
- I THINK THE CONTRACT
IS THE HEADLINE OF THIS.

06:54.620 --> 06:57.134
- WE REALLY APPRECIATE YOU GUYS
LETTING US COME BY.

06:57.170 --> 06:59.616
- WELL, WE REALLY
APPRECIATE YOU GUYS COMING BY.

06:59.660 --> 07:01.992
SYDNEY FEELS AWFUL
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED AT SCHOOL,

07:02.040 --> 07:04.440
SO SHE JUST WANTED TO
APOLOGIZE.

07:04.940 --> 07:06.202
GO AHEAD.

07:06.250 --> 07:07.729
- SYD.

07:09.980 --> 07:13.006
- I'M SORRY I TOLD EVERYONE
AT LUNCH NOT TO SIT WITH YOU.

07:15.050 --> 07:16.631
- SYD, TRY IT AGAIN.

07:16.670 --> 07:18.012
- WHAT? I CLEARLY APOLOGIZED.

07:18.050 --> 07:19.460
NOW I JUST WANT TO GO HOME.
- SYDNEY.

07:19.500 --> 07:20.944
- SYDNEY.

07:20.990 --> 07:22.878
SYDNEY, COME BACK HERE. SYD.

07:22.920 --> 07:24.080
- WELL, THAT WAS SINCERE.

07:24.130 --> 07:25.199
- YEAH.

07:25.230 --> 07:26.197
WE WILL TALK TO HER.

07:26.230 --> 07:27.367
- GREAT. YOU'LL TALK TO HER,

07:27.410 --> 07:30.026
SO THAT I CAN GET ANOTHER BOGUS
APOLOGY FOR MY DAUGHTER?

07:30.070 --> 07:32.265
NO. WHAT I WANT
IS YOUR ASSURANCE

07:32.310 --> 07:33.538
THAT THIS IS NEVER
GONNA HAPPEN AGAIN.

07:33.590 --> 07:35.967
- HONEY.

07:36.000 --> 07:37.888
MELODY, WOULD YOU GO UPSTAIRS
FOR A SECOND, PLEASE?

07:38.970 --> 07:40.107
- I'M SO SORRY, MELODY.

07:41.900 --> 07:44.482
- YOUR DAUGHTER
IS OUT OF CONTROL.

07:44.530 --> 07:45.599
- OKAY.

07:45.630 --> 07:47.006
I UNDERSTAND YOU GUYS ARE UPSET.

07:47.050 --> 07:49.075
SHE'S CLEARLY GOING
THROUGH A TOUGH TIME RIGHT NOW.

07:49.120 --> 07:51.213
- I DON'T NEED TO HEAR ABOUT
YOUR DAUGHTER'S TOUGH TIME.

07:51.260 --> 07:52.284
I'M SORRY.
I DON'T CARE ABOUT THAT.

07:52.330 --> 07:53.558
- I'M SO SORRY.
- WELL, MAYBE YOU

07:53.610 --> 07:56.181
NEED TO STOP BEING SORRY AND,
LIKE, DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT.

07:56.230 --> 07:57.151
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT ELSE TO TELL YOU.

07:57.200 --> 07:59.668
- ALL RIGHT.
- I AM SO SORRY.

07:59.720 --> 08:01.472
TRULY, I'M VERY SORRY.

08:02.820 --> 08:08.133
I'M GONNA GO TALK TO HER.

08:08.170 --> 08:09.478
- APOLOGIES AGAIN.

08:14.730 --> 08:17.039
- HEY, HONEY,
LOOK WHAT I GOT.

08:17.080 --> 08:19.139
FOR WHEN I'M UPSTAIRS OR AROUND
THE BACK OR SOMETHING,

08:19.180 --> 08:21.182
SO YOU WON'T HAVE TO YELL,
JUST RING.

08:21.220 --> 08:22.801
[bell jingles]

08:22.840 --> 08:26.150
GOOD IDEA?

08:26.190 --> 08:29.182
OR NOT.
WHAT ABOUT THIS?

08:29.230 --> 08:31.676
HAVE YOU DONE THIS?

08:31.710 --> 08:35.123
HAVE YOU EVEN
MOVED FROM THAT SPOT?

08:35.160 --> 08:36.297
COME ON.

08:36.340 --> 08:37.671
I WAS GONNA GET SOME FRESH AIR.

08:37.720 --> 08:39.267
- I'M WATCHING
THE JOHN WAYNE MARATHON.

08:39.310 --> 08:42.029
IT JUST STARTED.
DON'T MAKE ME YELL.

08:42.070 --> 08:43.549
- YEAH, WELL,
IT'S A GOOD THING WE HAVE TIVO.

08:43.590 --> 08:44.750
COME ON. LET'S GO.

08:44.800 --> 08:46.176
STRETCH YOUR LEGS.

08:46.210 --> 08:47.245
- WHAT HAPPENED TO,

08:47.280 --> 08:49.032
"YOU GO
AT YOUR OWN PACE, ZEEK.

08:49.080 --> 08:50.274
JUST TAKE YOUR TIME?"

08:50.320 --> 08:51.412
WHAT HAPPENED TO THAT?
- BECAUSE THE DOCTOR

08:51.460 --> 08:54.861
SAID WE HAVE TO BUILD UP
TO A WALK AROUND THE BLOCK.

08:54.910 --> 08:56.184
- WE--THE DOCTOR THE SAYS--
THE "WE" HAS GOT TO STOP.

08:56.220 --> 08:57.209
IT'S NOT "WE".

08:57.260 --> 08:59.148
IT'S ME, ALL RIGHT?

08:59.190 --> 09:01.875
IT'S MY THING, AND HE SAID
TAKE IT AT YOUR OWN PACE,

09:01.920 --> 09:03.364
AND RIGHT NOW MY PACE

09:03.400 --> 09:06.085
IS I'M GONNA WATCH
JOHN WAYNE BLOW SOMETHING UP.

09:06.130 --> 09:10.169
- OKAY, THEN WHY DON'T WE JUST
WALK HERE SOMEWHERE?

09:10.200 --> 09:12.361
LET'S WALK AROUND THE COUCH.
- WHAT?

09:12.410 --> 09:13.957
- WE'LL TAKE A LITTLE WALK
AROUND THE COUCH.

09:14.000 --> 09:15.308
- WHY THE HELL--I MEAN, WHY--

09:16.170 --> 09:18.206
WALK AROUND THE COUCH?

09:18.240 --> 09:20.174
- WELL, BECAUSE YOU GOT TO--

09:20.210 --> 09:21.825
YOU GOT TO START MOVING.

09:21.870 --> 09:24.247
- IF YOU WANT
TO RUN AROUND HERE,

09:24.280 --> 09:25.838
YOU JUST KNOCK YOURSELF OUT.

09:25.870 --> 09:27.007
YOU GO RIGHT AHEAD,

09:27.040 --> 09:30.112
BUT JUST DUCK
WHEN YOU GO BY THE TV.

09:34.190 --> 09:36.943
- HOW HOT DOES IT GET
AROUND HERE?

09:36.990 --> 09:39.185
- OH, 90.

09:39.230 --> 09:42.336
- KIARA, JUSTIN, EDGAR,
AARON, YOU GUYS ROCKED IT TODAY.

09:42.370 --> 09:44.292
- IS THIS PORK OR TURKEY?
- THAT IS PORK.

09:44.340 --> 09:46.160
AND, EDGAR, YOU CHOPPED
THOSE ONIONS SO FINE,

09:46.200 --> 09:47.303
WE ARE GONNA
CALL YOU THE CHOPPER, ALL RIGHT?

09:47.340 --> 09:48.750
- MR. BRAVERMAN--
- I WANT A NICKNAME.

09:48.790 --> 09:49.950
- OH, JUST A SECOND KIARA.
YOU WANT A NICKNAME?

09:50.000 --> 09:50.648
- YEAH.
- MR. BRAVERMAN--

09:50.690 --> 09:51.611
- YOU'RE THE PRINCE OF PEAS.

09:51.660 --> 09:53.161
- ONE SECOND, KIARA.
- THIS IS SUCCOTASH.

09:53.210 --> 09:55.132
- IT IS SUCCOTASH.
YOU'RE SUCCOTASH NASH.

09:55.180 --> 09:56.204
- I WANT ONE.
- MR. BRAVERMAN--

09:56.250 --> 09:58.172
- WHAT DO YOU WANT IT TO BE?

09:58.210 --> 09:59.142
- GINGERBREAD MAN.
- YOU'RE THE GINGERBREAD MAN.

09:59.180 --> 10:00.966
- MR. BRAVERMAN--
- HOW ABOUT YOU, KIARA?

10:01.010 --> 10:01.863
- I DON'T WANT A NICKNAME.
- YOU DON'T WANT A NICKNAME?

10:01.910 --> 10:02.979
HOW COME?
- THEY PROMOTE FAVORITISM.

10:03.010 --> 10:05.149
- OKAY, THEN YOU DON'T HAVE
TO HAVE A NICKNAME.

10:05.190 --> 10:06.009
GUYS, GRAB YOURSELF SOME LUNCH.

10:06.050 --> 10:08.086
YOU GUYS WERE JUST ON POINT
TODAY.

10:08.120 --> 10:09.257
AWESOME.

10:09.290 --> 10:10.393
HEY.

10:10.430 --> 10:11.670
- HEY.

10:11.710 --> 10:13.189
- MY KITCHEN IS HUMMING.
- I KNOW.

10:13.230 --> 10:15.016
IT LOOKS GOOD IN THERE.
- THESE GUYS ARE LOCKED IN.

10:15.060 --> 10:16.152
- LOCKED IN.
- YOU KNOW THAT?

10:16.200 --> 10:17.815
- YEAH.
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

10:18.990 --> 10:20.298
- JUST CHECKING OUT
THE NEW GIRL.

