13:22.870 --> 13:25.134
GO UP THERE, GET A MASSAGE...
- MM-HMM.

13:25.180 --> 13:27.933
- SEAWEED WRAP OR SOMETHING.

13:27.970 --> 13:30.973
- WELL, I MEAN, I GUESS
THE RIDE THERE WILL BE RELAXING,

13:31.010 --> 13:33.217
WHICH IS MAYBE THE ONLY UPSIDE.

13:33.260 --> 13:35.353
- THE DRIVE.
THE DRIVE THERE.

13:35.400 --> 13:38.016
- NO, NO. I'M GONNA RIDE--
I'M GONNA RIDE THE MOTORCYCLE.

13:38.050 --> 13:39.392
IT'S PACIFIC COAST HIGHWAY
BY THE WOODS.

13:39.430 --> 13:41.250
- NO, NO.
YOU'RE GONNA DRIVE THE MINIVAN.

13:41.300 --> 13:42.574
YOU'RE NOT RIDING
THE MOTORCYCLE.

13:42.610 --> 13:44.919
WE JUST HAD
THAT DISCUSSION EARLIER TODAY.

13:44.960 --> 13:47.099
- NO, NO,
NO, WE DISCUSSED THAT THE BOY

13:47.130 --> 13:48.540
COULDN'T RIDE THE MOTORCYCLE,

13:48.580 --> 13:50.855
BUT I, AS A GROWN-ASS MAN,

13:50.890 --> 13:51.993
AM GONNA RIDE THE MOTORCYCLE.

13:52.030 --> 13:54.407
- NO, YOU'RE GONNA
DRIVE THE MINIVAN.

13:54.450 --> 13:57.101
- I AM NOT DRIVING THE MINIVAN.
- REALLY?

13:57.140 --> 14:00.075
- THERE'S NO WORLD IN WHICH I
AM DRIVING THAT MINIVAN.

14:00.110 --> 14:02.101
- CHICKEN FRIED CHICKEN
FOR MY LI'ITLE NUGGET.

14:02.150 --> 14:04.869
- CROSBY'S GONNA GO TRY
AND FIND HIM AND TALK TO HIM.

14:04.910 --> 14:06.241
- I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW YOU GUYS

14:06.290 --> 14:07.450
DON'T HAVE A CONTRACT
WITH HIM.

14:07.500 --> 14:08.899
IT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

14:08.950 --> 14:11.669
- MY LOCKER STICKS ON 23,
AND ALGEBRA SUCKS.

14:11.710 --> 14:13.428
- DON'T SAY "SUCKS".
THAT'S A--

14:13.470 --> 14:14.630
- THAT'S RIGHT.
DON'T SAY "SUCKS".

14:14.680 --> 14:15.817
- IT'S A BAD WORD.
- WHY CAN YOU SAY SUCKS?

14:15.850 --> 14:17.533
- DON'T SAY BAD WORDS
IN FRONT OF YOUR LI'ITLE SISTER.

14:17.580 --> 14:19.059
- "SUCKS" IS A VERB.
- HONEY, "SUCKS" IS A BAD WORD.

14:19.090 --> 14:20.534
- MAX, GO WORK ON YOUR LOCKER.
- HEY...

14:20.580 --> 14:22.059
I SAW YOU SITTING
WITH DYLAN TODAY,

14:22.100 --> 14:23.362
THE NEW GIRL, AT LUNCH.
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

14:23.410 --> 14:25.503
- SHE SEEMS LIKE
A VERY NICE GIRL.

14:25.550 --> 14:27.029
I'M HIS MOM.
I WANT TO ASK HIM, OKAY?

14:27.070 --> 14:27.855
I'M OFF THE CLOCK, RIGHT?

14:27.900 --> 14:29.413
- SHE CALLS ME ASPERGER'S,
NOT MAX.

14:29.450 --> 14:32.066
- WAIT--WHAT?
- WHAT?

14:32.110 --> 14:33.247
- SHE SAYS SHE KNOWS
THAT I HAVE ASPERGER'S

14:33.280 --> 14:36.909
BECAUSE I DON'T MAKE EYE CONTACT
AND I SAY WEIRD THINGS.

14:36.940 --> 14:39.170
SHE ALSO SAYS MY ASPERGER'S IS
WHAT MAKES ME WEIRD.

14:39.220 --> 14:41.142
- SHE'S DOESN'T CALL YOU MAX?
SHE SAYS, "HEY, ASPERGER'S"?

14:41.190 --> 14:42.669
- YES, THAT IS EXACTLY
WHAT SHE SAYS.

14:42.700 --> 14:43.940
- THAT'S NOT APPROPRIATE.
- THAT'S ACTUALLY UNACCEPTABLE,

14:43.980 --> 14:45.254
SO I'LL HAVE A TALK WITH HER.
- IT'S TIME TO CALL YOU MAX.

14:45.290 --> 14:46.018
- I MENTIONED IT, BUT SHE SAYS
SHE LIKE CALLING ME ASPERGER'S.

14:46.050 --> 14:49.087
SHE ALSO CALLS ME FREAK.
- WHAT?

14:49.120 --> 14:50.508
- AND SHE SAYS
THAT CHAMBERS ACADEMY

14:50.540 --> 14:52.644
IS A POTPOU'D'F! OF FREAKS.

14:52.680 --> 14:54.568
- SHE SAID IT WAS A POTPOURRI
OF FREAKS?

14:54.610 --> 14:56.020
- THOSE WERE HER EXACT WORDS.
- VERY INAPPROPRIATE.

14:56.060 --> 14:57.163
- OKAY.
- AND SHE ALSO AGREES WITH ME

14:57.200 --> 14:58.952
THAT WE SHOULD BE ABLE
TO GO OFF CAMPUS FOR LUNCH,

14:59.000 --> 15:01.139
ESPECIALLY SINCE THERE'S
A CHIPOTLE TWO BLOCKS AWAY...

15:01.170 --> 15:02.614
- NOT GONNA HAPPEN.
- AND THAT CHAMBERS ACADEMY

15:02.660 --> 15:04.412
IS THE EQUIVALENT
OF A MINIMUM SECURITY PRISON

15:04.450 --> 15:05.417
BECAUSE THEY DON'T
LET US LEAVE.

15:05.450 --> 15:06.929
- SOUNDS LIKE SHE HAD
QUITE A CONVERSATION

15:06.970 --> 15:07.959
WITH YOU, DIDN'T SHE?
- WOW. LOUDMOUTH.

15:08.010 --> 15:09.272
- ALSO, SINCE MY PARENTS
ARE THE ADMINISTRATORS,

15:09.320 --> 15:11.936
I SHOULD BE ABLE TO GET SPECIAL
TREATMENT, LIKE LUNCH FOR LIFE.

15:11.980 --> 15:12.935
- SHE'S--
- AND IF I CAN'T,

15:12.980 --> 15:13.935
I SHOULD STICK IT TO THE MAN,

15:13.980 --> 15:17.040
AND YOU'RE THE MAN,
MOM--IN THAT SITUATION.

15:17.080 --> 15:18.661
- YOU'RE THE MAN.

15:22.050 --> 15:24.678
[door opens]

15:24.710 --> 15:26.268
- HEY. STILL HERE?

15:26.300 --> 15:28.291
- YEAH, I WAS
WAITING FOR YOU.

15:28.340 --> 15:30.365
- OH, HUH.
YOU NEVER DO THAT.

15:30.410 --> 15:33.231
- WELL, YOU HAD A COUPLE
OF MESSAGES WHILE YOU WERE OUT--

15:33.270 --> 15:34.953
I WANTED TO DELIVER PERSONALLY.

15:35.000 --> 15:36.331
EYE DOCTOR CALLED.

15:36.380 --> 15:38.234
YOU'RE DUE FOR A CHECKUP.
- OH. YEAH.

15:38.280 --> 15:41.272
- ELLIE PATEL IS CHANGING
HER SHOOT DAY.

15:41.310 --> 15:44.199
OH, AND YOUR EX-WIFE CAME BY.

15:44.250 --> 15:45.524
HEH.

15:45.560 --> 15:48.176
- CAME BY HERE WHEN--YOU TWO?
- YEAH, SHE WAS LOOKING FOR YOU.

15:48.220 --> 15:50.279
YEAH, WE HAD A NICE LITTLE CHAT.

15:50.320 --> 15:52.288
- HUH.

15:52.330 --> 15:53.979
THAT'S NOT AN IMAGE I LIKE.

15:54.020 --> 15:55.180
- YEAH.

15:55.230 --> 15:57.607
- ALL RIGHT, LOOK--LISTEN,
LISTEN, LISTEN--SHE'S CRAZY.

15:57.640 --> 15:59.221
OKAY?

15:59.260 --> 16:02.263
SO ANYTHING THAT SHE SAYS,
YOU JUST GOT A GRAIN OF SALT IT.

16:02.300 --> 16:04.643
- SO SHE DIDN'T MEAN IT AT ALL
WHEN SHE SAID

16:04.680 --> 16:08.309
THAT SHE DOESN'T WANT
ME SPENDING ANY TIME WITH RUBY?

16:08.340 --> 16:10.683
- NO, SHE MEANT THAT.
- OKAY.

16:10.720 --> 16:13.029
BUT WHY WOULDN'T YOU TELL ME
THAT YOU HAD THAT CONVERSATION?

16:13.070 --> 16:14.298
- AND IT'S--
- SHE SAID SHE TOLD YOU THAT,

16:14.350 --> 16:16.409
AND I GUESS
YOU WERE OKAY WITH IT.

16:16.450 --> 16:21.171
- I'M JUST TRYING TO KEEP
EVERYBODY HAPPY AND SEPARATE.

16:21.220 --> 16:23.359
- I DON'T THINK
YOU CAN KEEP THINGS SEPARATE.

16:23.390 --> 16:25.278
WE'RE--YOU CAN'T KEEP EVERYONE
JUST, IN THEIR OWN LITTLE BOX.

16:25.320 --> 16:27.049
- WELL, WHAT DO I GOT
TO TELL HER ANYTHING FOR?

16:27.080 --> 16:29.082
IT'S MY RELATIONSHIP.
IT'S OUR RELATIONSHIP.

16:29.120 --> 16:30.769
- BECAUSE SHE SEEMS TO THINK
I'M SOME SORT OF ASSISTANT

16:30.810 --> 16:32.778
WITH SPECIAL BENEFITS.
- WELL, SHE'S WRONG.

16:32.810 --> 16:34.778
- I MEAN, SHE'S GOT
THE WRONG IDEA ABOUT ME.

16:34.820 --> 16:36.219
- OF COURSE SHE HAS THE WRONG
IDEA, 'CAUSE SHE'S CRAZY.

16:36.270 --> 16:37.817
- OKAY, WELL,
NOBODY CAN READ YOUR MIND,

16:37.850 --> 16:39.818
SO IT MIGHT BE
THE KIND OF THING

16:39.860 --> 16:42.328
THAT IS IMPORTANT
TO TALK ABOUT.

16:42.380 --> 16:43.824
- I CAN'T.
SHE JUST--

16:43.860 --> 16:48.752
- MM-HMM?

16:48.800 --> 16:50.722
- I GO IN, AND I THINK
I KNOW WHAT I WANT TO SAY,

16:50.760 --> 16:54.457
AND SHE JUST KEEPS TALKING
AND TALKING,

16:54.490 --> 16:56.378
AND SUDDENLY I'M AGREEING
TO THINGS

16:56.420 --> 17:00.834
THAT I DON'T EVEN UNDERSTAND.

17:00.880 --> 17:03.496
I CAN'T TALK TO HER.

17:10.780 --> 17:13.476
I'LL TALK TO HER.

17:13.510 --> 17:15.785
THAT'S WHAT I'LL DO.
HOW HARD CAN IT BE?

17:15.820 --> 17:18.129
- AND WHEN RON SAID
SHE WAS OUT OF CONTROL--

17:18.170 --> 17:19.785
- I KNOW.

17:19.830 --> 17:21.616
- MAYBE WE SHOULD TALK
TO THE THERAPIST, OR--

17:21.660 --> 17:24.823
- NO, I DON'T THINK SO. ITHINK
SHE IS OUT OF CONTROL, THOUGH.

17:24.870 --> 17:26.792
'CAUSE WE'RE OUT OF CONTROL.

17:26.830 --> 17:29.651
I MEAN, WHAT ARE WE DOING?

17:29.700 --> 17:32.168
I DON'T KNOW.
ARE WE STALLING?

17:32.220 --> 17:36.566
THE UNCERTAINTY OF US
IS TOO MUCH FOR HER.

17:36.600 --> 17:38.875
- I GET IT.
IT'S BEEN HARD ON BOTH THE KIDS,

17:38.910 --> 17:43.199
BUT, YOU KNOW, WE'RE DOING
THE BEST WE CAN HERE.

17:43.230 --> 17:45.744
- I DON'T--I MEAN,
I THOUGHT THAT YOU MOVING OUT

17:45.780 --> 17:47.293
WOULD BE THE HARDEST PART
OF THIS FOR THEM,

17:47.340 --> 17:49.786
BUT THIS IS WORSE.

17:49.820 --> 17:52.573
THEY'RE JUST IN LIMBO.

17:52.620 --> 17:55.828
WE--WE HAVE TO GIVE
THEM SOME CLARITY.

18:00.630 --> 18:02.586
[dog barking]

18:02.630 --> 18:05.793
OKAY?

18:05.840 --> 18:08.456
- HEH.

18:08.500 --> 18:10.218
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

18:15.810 --> 18:17.778
- OKAY, WE NEED TO TELL THEM

18:17.820 --> 18:19.776
WE'RE NOT GETTING BACK
TOGETHER.

18:28.270 --> 18:33.515
- YOU READY--YOU READY
TO SAY THAT TO THEM?

18:52.610 --> 18:55.738
- YO, ASPERGER'S,
WHAT'S UP?

18:55.780 --> 18:59.853
- HEY, DYLAN, CAN YOU PLEASE
COME HERE FOR A MOMENT?

18:59.890 --> 19:01.778
- IS THIS MY FIRST TRIP
TO THE OFFICE?

19:03.790 --> 19:04.859
- CAN YOU HAVE A SEAT?

19:04.900 --> 19:06.822
- OH, I PREFER TO STAND.

19:06.860 --> 19:07.827
- I'M SORRY?

19:07.870 --> 19:09.826
- I PREFER TO STAND.

19:09.870 --> 19:11.178
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

19:11.210 --> 19:12.381
- OKAY, WELL,
I'M GONNA HAVE A SEAT.

19:12.420 --> 19:15.309
- OKAY.
- SO, HERE'S THE THING, HONEY.

