AT CHAMBERS ACADEMY, WE DON'T
CALL EACH OTHER NAMES, OKAY?

19:18.740 --> 19:20.423
WE TREAT EACH OTHER
WITH KINDNESS,

19:20.460 --> 19:22.701
AND RESPECT, AND DIGNITY.
- UH-HUH.

19:22.740 --> 19:24.423
- OKAY, DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN DO THAT?

19:24.470 --> 19:25.914
- SURE.
- PERFECT.

19:25.950 --> 19:28.327
- BUT I DIDN'T DISRESPECT MAX.
- WELL--

19:28.370 --> 19:29.814
- NO, YOUR SON HAS ASPERGER'S.

19:29.850 --> 19:31.124
THAT'S JUST A SIMPLE FACT.
I MEAN,

19:31.170 --> 19:33.229
I THOUGHT WE WERE SUPPOSED TO
CELEBRATE OUR DIFFERENCES HERE.

19:33.270 --> 19:35.579
LOOK, I THINK THE REAL PROBLEM
IS ATTACHING STIGMA TO THE WORD.

19:35.620 --> 19:37.338
THAT'S WHAT MAKES IT
DEROGATORY.

19:37.380 --> 19:38.779
ASPERGER'S BY ITSELF--

19:38.830 --> 19:40.821
THAT'S JUST A DSM-5 DIAGNOSIS,
KRISTINA.

19:40.860 --> 19:42.930
- ACTUALLY, IT USED TO BE
A DSM-4 DIAGNOSIS,

19:42.970 --> 19:44.858
BUT IT'S NOT ANYMORE.
AND DON'T CALL ME KRISTINA.

19:44.900 --> 19:45.969
CALL ME MRS. BRAVERMAN.

19:46.010 --> 19:48.934
