32:22.250 --> 32:25.037
I MEAN, WE SHOULD HAVE
LEI-T THE BED UPSTAIRS.

32:25.080 --> 32:27.002
- WHY?
THAT WAS A GOOD IDEA.

32:27.040 --> 32:29.076
- BECAUSE THEN HE'D HAVE
TO MOVE.

32:29.110 --> 32:30.429
HE'D HAVE TO MOVE.

32:30.460 --> 32:32.075
NOW HE GOES FROM THE BED
TO THE COUCH,

32:32.120 --> 32:33.348
BACK TO THE BED AGAIN.

32:33.390 --> 32:35.278
- MM-HMM.
- WE MADE IT TOO EASY ON HIM.

32:35.330 --> 32:36.638
- JUST GIVE IT
A LITTLE MORE TIME.

32:36.670 --> 32:37.739
HE'LL GET THERE.

32:37.780 --> 32:41.398
- OH, ADAM,
ALL OUR LIFE TOGETHER,

32:41.440 --> 32:45.262
THERE WAS NOT EVER
A PHYSICAL CHALLENGE

32:45.300 --> 32:46.540
THAT HE WOULDN'T TACKLE.

32:46.580 --> 32:49.128
- RIGHT.

32:49.170 --> 32:52.162
- NOW HE JUST SITS THERE.

32:54.310 --> 32:57.723
I THOUGHT THE HARD PART OF THIS
WAS GONNA BE KEEPING HIM DOWN.

32:57.760 --> 32:59.648
- MOM, HE'S GONNA GET STRONGER.

32:59.700 --> 33:05.218
IT'S JUST TAKING HIM LONGER.

33:05.250 --> 33:07.389
- I THINK HE'S AFRAID TO TRY.

33:13.710 --> 33:18.409
I'M AFRAID HE'S GIVING UP.

33:18.440 --> 33:20.431
- OH, MOM. COME ON.

33:24.100 --> 33:25.306
COME HERE.

33:25.340 --> 33:27.820
COME HERE, MOM.

33:27.860 --> 33:30.203
- [sniffles]

33:30.240 --> 33:33.721
- IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

33:40.290 --> 33:42.451
- YEAH, SO, IT'S KIND
OF A FIRST FOR ME, YOU KNOW?

33:42.500 --> 33:43.706
NICE.
- YEAH.

33:43.740 --> 33:46.322
- I MEAN, I SAID MORE WORDS
THAN HER, BELIEVE IT OR NOT,

33:46.360 --> 33:48.089
AND THEY ALL KIND OF
MADE SENSE.

33:48.120 --> 33:50.816
- HEY. GOOD JOB.

33:50.850 --> 33:52.431
- YEAH, ALL RIGHT.
- REALLY.

33:52.470 --> 33:54.222
- DON'T--I'M NOT GONNA
MAKE A BIG DEAL ABOUT IT.

33:54.270 --> 33:56.124
- IT'S A BIG DEAL.
- WELL, I'M GLAD.

33:56.170 --> 33:58.058
I'M GLAD YOU'RE, YOU KNOW--

33:58.100 --> 33:59.510
YOU'RE OUT OF THE BOX NOW.

33:59.550 --> 34:02.064
- I'M OUT OF THE BOX. YEAH.
- YOU KNOW?

34:02.100 --> 34:03.727
I MEAN, BETWEEN YOU AND RUBY--
[knock on door]

34:03.760 --> 34:07.480
OKAY. HEY.

34:07.520 --> 34:08.691
- HEY. HI.

34:08.730 --> 34:09.412
- HI.
- HEY.

34:09.460 --> 34:11.348
- HEY, DAD.
- HEY, KIDDO.

34:11.390 --> 34:13.767
- NICE TO SEE YOU, SARAH.
- NICE TO SEE YOU, SANDY.

34:13.810 --> 34:14.765
HELLO.

34:14.810 --> 34:16.186
- ALL RIGHT, SWEETIE. HAVE FUN.
- ALL RIGHT.

34:16.220 --> 34:19.212
- OKAY. GOOD LUCK.

34:19.260 --> 34:20.329
- HEY, DID YOU WANT TO--

34:20.360 --> 34:21.679
YEAH, HELP YOURSELF.

34:21.710 --> 34:25.396
SO, RUBY,
I THOUGHT WE'D DO A PIZZA NIGHT.

34:25.440 --> 34:26.884
YOU CAN--ANY TOPPINGS YOU WANT.

34:26.920 --> 34:29.366
YOU CAN DO, LIKE,
A MEAT LOVER, CHEESE LOVER--

34:29.410 --> 34:31.093
- I DON'T DO DAIRY.

34:31.130 --> 34:32.301
- OH, DAMN.
STILL?

34:32.340 --> 34:33.500
SEE, I THOUGHT--I KNEW THAT--

34:33.550 --> 34:35.097
AH, SHE JUST HAS--
- THAT'S OKAY.

34:35.140 --> 34:36.129
WELL, THERE'S PLENTY OF STUFF
THAT ISN'T DAIRY.

34:36.170 --> 34:37.853
- CHEESELESS--YOU EVER
HAD A CH EESELESS PIZZA--

34:37.900 --> 34:39.231
WHICH IS REALLY BREAD?
- EXACTLY. YES.

34:39.280 --> 34:41.896
- WHAT ARE YOU WEARING?
- WHAT?

34:41.940 --> 34:43.862
- IS THAT FOREVER 21?

34:43.900 --> 34:49.349
- NO. IT'S SOMETIMES 40,
I GUESS.

34:49.390 --> 34:53.349
- NICE TRY.
- THANKS.

34:53.400 --> 34:56.779
- IT'S A VALIANT EFFORT.

34:56.810 --> 34:58.675
- WHAT IS--WHAT'S MAYBE 20?
WHAT IS IT?

34:58.710 --> 35:02.259
- IT'S NOT A COMPLIMENT.

35:02.300 --> 35:04.541
- I MEAN, YOU LOOK--
YOU LOOK FINE TO ME.

35:04.580 --> 35:05.854
[door closes]
YOU--

35:05.890 --> 35:07.881
- DON'T.

35:13.420 --> 35:15.559
- HEY, BUD.
CAN WE TALK FOR A SECOND?

35:15.590 --> 35:18.866
- NO.
THIS IS MY SCREEN TIME.

35:18.900 --> 35:21.596
- I WILL CREDIT
YOU ONE HOUR, OKAY?

35:22.810 --> 35:24.835
- THAT'S FAIR.

35:24.880 --> 35:29.158
- ALL RIGHT, GOOD.
SO, WHAT'S GOING ON AT SCHOOL?

35:29.190 --> 35:30.919
- WHY DO YOU AND MOM
KEEP ASKING ME THAT?

35:30.950 --> 35:32.565
- WELL, IT'S A NEW SITUATION.

35:32.610 --> 35:34.430
I WANT YOU TO KNOW YOU
CAN TALK TO ME ABOUT ANYTHING

35:34.470 --> 35:36.745
THAT IS OF INTEREST TO YOU,

35:36.780 --> 35:41.126
OR IF SOMETHING'S BOTHERING YOU
AT SCHOOL--OR SOMEONE.

35:45.690 --> 35:49.274
LIKE, MAYBE DYLAN?

35:49.310 --> 35:52.791
OR IF IT'S OKAY,
THEN IT'S OKAY.

35:52.840 --> 35:56.458
- ARE YOU HERE AS
AN ADMINISTRATOR OR AS A PARENT?

35:56.490 --> 35:57.969
- I'M HERE AS YOUR DAD, MAX--

35:58.010 --> 36:00.387
JUST AS YOUR DAD.

36:00.430 --> 36:02.182
- THEN I DO HAVE ONE QUESTION.

36:02.220 --> 36:03.630
- ALL RIGHT.

36:03.670 --> 36:07.879
ANYTHING. GO AHEAD, SHOOT.

36:07.920 --> 36:10.844
- WHAT DO YOU DO
WHEN YOU LIKE A GIRL?

36:16.820 --> 36:21.848
- UM...OKAY.

36:21.900 --> 36:24.755
- I ONLY HAD TWO PIECES.

36:24.800 --> 36:25.960
- I THINK I HAD SEVEN.
HOW MANY DID YOU HAVE?

36:26.010 --> 36:26.931
- DAD.

36:26.970 --> 36:28.858
- HEY.

36:28.910 --> 36:31.970
- HEY, YOU LEI-T THIS IN THE BACK
OF THE TRUCK.

36:32.010 --> 36:32.908
- OKAY.
- HEY, DAD.

36:32.940 --> 36:34.077
- I KNOW YOU WANT IT
FOR THE BIG GAME,

36:34.120 --> 36:36.566
AND--OH, BY THE WAY, I
DIDN'T SEE YOUR GLOVE IN THERE,

36:36.600 --> 36:37.840
SO YOU MAY WANT TO CHECK IT.
- OH, OKAY.

36:37.880 --> 36:39.222
- I'LL SEE YOU LATER SOMETIME.
- COOL ENOUGH.

36:39.260 --> 36:41.319
ARE YOU STAYING FOR DINNER, OR--

36:41.370 --> 36:42.985
- NO, BUDDY.
I'M NOT STAYING.

36:43.020 --> 36:44.908
- OKAY.

36:44.960 --> 36:47.849
- WHEN ARE YOU
GONNA STAY, DAD?

36:47.890 --> 36:49.471
- WELL--

36:49.510 --> 36:50.852
- SYDNEY, COME HERE.
COME HERE.

36:54.930 --> 36:56.579
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN TO ME.

36:56.620 --> 36:57.723
I KNOW IT'S HARD

36:57.760 --> 37:02.038
NOT KNOWING WHAT'S HAPPENING
WITH ME AND YOUR DAD.

37:02.080 --> 37:05.664
WE'VE BEEN TALKING ABOUT THAT,

37:05.700 --> 37:08.669
AND--
- HEY.

37:08.700 --> 37:10.429
- AND WE'RE SORRY.

37:10.460 --> 37:13.805
I WISH I COULD JUST TELL
YOU RIGHT NOW WHAT'S HAPPENING,

37:13.850 --> 37:17.889
BUT THE TRUTH
IS THAT WE DON'T KNOW.

37:23.750 --> 37:24.956
WE JUST REALLY
WANT TO MAKE THE RIGHT DECISION,

37:25.000 --> 37:28.891
AND WE DON'T KNOW
WHAT THAT IS, SO--

37:28.930 --> 37:33.412
OH, SWEETHEART,
YOU AND ME ARE SO ALIKE.

37:33.450 --> 37:36.999
I KNOW I HATE UNCERTAINTY.

37:37.040 --> 37:38.928
I HATE FEELING
LIKE I'M OUT OF CONTROL.

37:38.980 --> 37:40.663
I--SWEETIE, I'M SORRY.

37:40.700 --> 37:42.941
IT'S JUST--

37:42.980 --> 37:45.631
- IT'S JUST THE WAY IT IS,
BUG, I'M SORRY TOO.

37:45.670 --> 37:47.877
IT'S JUST--I KNOW,
BUT IT'S SOMETHING

37:47.920 --> 37:48.989
THAT GROWN-UPS
ARE TRYING TO FIGURE OUT.

37:49.020 --> 37:51.773
- HEY, SYD, SYD, DON'T RUN
AWAY FROM THIS, PLEASE.

37:51.820 --> 37:53.879
- I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT ANYMORE.

37:53.920 --> 37:55.364
- OKAY, WE DON'T HAVE TO
TALK ABOUT IT ANYMORE.

37:55.410 --> 37:59.540
I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT IF YOU'RE MAD AT ME,

37:59.580 --> 38:02.401
IT'S OKAY.

38:02.450 --> 38:03.963
AND IF YOU'RE MAD AT DAD,

38:04.000 --> 38:06.685
IT'S OKAY.

38:06.730 --> 38:09.585
ALL RIGHT,
WE'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

38:19.080 --> 38:22.083
[minivan pulls up]

38:25.950 --> 38:27.952
[door opens and closes]

38:41.970 --> 38:43.961
[motorcycle rewing]

38:51.120 --> 38:54.977
- HEY! CROSBY!

39:02.130 --> 39:04.098
[door opens]

39:04.130 --> 39:06.360
- OH, WELL, LOOK WHO'S HERE.

39:06.410 --> 39:08.810
- BOY, DO YOU LOOK LIFE CRAP.

39:08.860 --> 39:11.408
- YEAH, WELL--HEY,
DID YOU LEAVE THE DOOR OPEN?

39:11.450 --> 39:12.894
- I DID.

39:12.930 --> 39:14.488
- COULD YOU JUST TAKE YOUR ASS
RIGHT BACK OUT AGAIN?

39:14.520 --> 39:15.964
- I CAN CALL IT
LIKE I SEE IT, YOU KNOW?

39:16.000 --> 39:16.864
- YEAH, WELL,
LIKE YOU SEE IT--YEAH.

39:16.900 --> 39:19.937
- I HAD CANCER,
SO I GET A FREE PASS.

39:19.970 --> 39:21.938
- YOU'RE A BREATH OF FRESH AIR.

39:21.980 --> 39:23.834
I CAN TELL YOU THAT.

39:23.870 --> 39:25.451
- HOW YOU DOING?

39:25.500 --> 39:28.526
- WELL, KRISTINA,
I'VE BEEN BETTER.

39:28.570 --> 39:30.538
- SUCKS, DOESN'T IT?
- UH-HUH.

39:30.570 --> 39:31.912
- I THINK THE CRAPPIEST PART

39:31.950 --> 39:36.887
ABOUT BEING SICK
FOR ME WAS JUST THE PEOPLE.

39:36.920 --> 39:38.535
I KNOW IT SOUNDS SO WEIRD,

39:38.580 --> 39:41.128
BUT THE PEOPLE
JUST REALLY PISSED ME OFF.

39:41.170 --> 39:44.640
THE SAD FACES AND ALL THE PITY,

39:44.690 --> 39:46.851
AND THE FALSE SENSE OF CHEER--

39:46.900 --> 39:48.959
"WE CAN DO THIS."
THE "WE'S".

39:49.000 --> 39:50.206
- WE--WE--
- THE "WE'S".

39:50.240 --> 39:51.719
RIGHT?
- OH, YEAH.

39:51.760 --> 39:52.556
WE CAN WALK.
WE CAN--

39:52.590 --> 39:53.898
- WE CAN DO IT, RIGHT?

39:53.940 --> 39:55.931
- AND ALL THAT.

39:55.970 --> 39:58.768
- YEAH.

40:00.600 --> 40:01.828
I THINK THE HARDEST PART

40:01.880 --> 40:06.010
WAS JUST KNOWING HOW SICK
THAT I ACTUALLY WAS

40:06.050 --> 40:08.917
AND HOW I FELT SO AWFUL
ALL THE TIME,

40:08.950 --> 40:14.126
AND JUST HOW--
HOW SCARED I WAS.

40:14.170 --> 40:16.161
YOU KNOW?

40:22.000 --> 40:24.446
YOU KNOW, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO PRETEND

40:24.490 --> 40:25.889
TO BE STRONGER THAN YOU FEEL.
- GOD.

40:25.940 --> 40:27.828
- YOU DON'T.

40:27.870 --> 40:30.486
BUT YOU HAVE TO TRY
TO GET BETTER.

40:30.530 --> 40:33.112
- OH, GOD.
- YOU HAVE TO TRY.

40:33.150 --> 40:36.119
YOU GOT IT?
- YEAH.

40:36.150 --> 40:37.833
- 'CAUSE A LOT OF PEOPLE
ARE COUNTING ON YOU.

40:37.880 --> 40:42.010
- OKAY.

40:42.060 --> 40:44.506
OH, GOD.

40:44.540 --> 40:47.532
OKAY.

40:51.690 --> 40:55.968
GET ME UP.

40:56.000 --> 40:58.036
OKAY.

40:58.070 --> 41:00.277
- OKAY? COME ON.
- YEAH.

41:00.310 --> 41:05.589
- YOU'RE GONNA NEED

41:05.630 --> 41:12.638
ALL THE HELP
YOU CAN GET

41:12.840 --> 41:17.868
SO LII-T UP YOUR ARMS NOW

41:17.920 --> 41:24.928
AND REACH FOR IT

41:29.900 --> 41:33.927
AND WATCH THE SIGNS NOW

41:33.970 --> 41:35.858
YOU KNOW'LL
WHAT THEY MEAN

41:35.900 --> 41:38.869
YOU'LL BE FINE NOW

41:38.910 --> 41:41.663
JUST STAY CLOSE TO ME

41:41.700 --> 41:45.181
I'LL MAKE GOOD

41:45.220 --> 41:51.329
I'LL WALK WITH YOU
THROUGH EVERYTHING

41:51.370 --> 41:56.080
IN A SONG OF GOOD HOPE

41:56.130 --> 42:00.169
WALK WITH YOU
THROUGH EVERYTHING
